        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 3:52PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 352 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Graham Guard Station, or 24 miles southeast of Lowman,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Elmore
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
